  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0in 5.75pt 0in 5.75pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Weapon Preference: Torpedo and Bombardment weapons</=
p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Research Preference: Power and Shields</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>A very old race, from when the Galaxy was a lot hott=
er place
  to exist. Dark skinned reptiles, of average height but an outer skin that=
 is
  almost as tough as stone.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>Keskudons</span> believe this G=
alaxy is
  their own, they claim to be the first race to have ventured in to the sta=
rs
  and were once settlers over the whole galaxy. They will not reveal why th=
ey
  appear to be just now appearing though. <span class=3DSpellE>Keskudons</s=
pan>
  see all other races as trespassing, claiming rights on every system in the
  Galaxy.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Intelligent and very aggressive, <span class=3DSpell=
E>Keskudons</span>
  cannot be trusted as to them, all other life is considered as an infectio=
n.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>A slaver race, the <span class=3DSpellE>Keskudons</s=
pan>
  military leaders measure their prestige and influence based on how many
  slaves they own.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>Keskudons</span> make very poor=
 allies
  and are unlikely to seek any alliances other than to create a temporary c=
ease
  fire to gather for an assault later.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The <span class=3DSpellE>Keskudons</span> have the m=
ost
  advanced technology regarding fissile reactions. Their long history of us=
ing
  nuclear power has allowed them to develop the highly efficient Fissile
  Exploitation Reactor, gaining the efficiency other races can only gain
  through fusion reaction.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>Keskudons</span> prefer hotter
  climates. Without a relatively high amount of energy, they will become
  dormant and docile.</p>
